docs.snippet: Fears are growing that the festering turmoil in Ukraine and the new round of sanctions announced Tuesday will damage the economy to the extent that ordinary Russians feel it.
docs.lead_paragraph: Fears are growing that the festering turmoil in Ukraine and the new round of sanctions announced Tuesday will damage the economy to the extent that ordinary Russians feel it.
docs.abstract: There is growing alarm in Russia that turmoil in Ukraine and new round of far more punitive sanctions will have impact on its relations with the West for years to come and damage the economy to extent that ordinary Russians feel it; Pres Vladimir V Putin has so far adopted nonchalant public stance and, in a strategy that seems to be crumbling, has fed separatist insurgency in Ukraine without leaving distinct fingerprints.

headline.main: As Sanctions Pile Up, Russians’ Alarm Grows Over Putin’s Tactics
headline.print_headline: As Sanctions Pile Up, Russians’ Alarm Grows Over Putin Tactics

docs.snippet: A piece from the Malaysia Airlines plane in Ukraine, examined in photographs by defense consultants, had damage consistent with that from a fragmenting warhead, the kind carried by an SA-11 missile.
docs.lead_paragraph: A piece from the Malaysia Airlines plane in Ukraine, examined in photographs by defense consultants, had damage consistent with that from a fragmenting warhead, the kind carried by an SA-11 missile.
docs.abstract: Piece of wreckage from Malaysia Airlines Flight 17 bears telltale marks of small pieces of high-velocity shrapnel that apparently crippled jet in flight; wreckage suggests that destruction of aircraft was caused by supersonic missile that apparently exploded near the jet as it flew.

headline.main: Jet Wreckage Bears Signs of Impact by Supersonic Missile, Analysis Shows
headline.print_headline: Jet Wreckage Bears Signs of Impact by Supersonic Missile, Analysis Shows

docs.abstract: Russia is presenting combination of conciliation and bluster over its handling of downed Malaysia Airlines jet, with Pres Vladimir V Putin seemingly probing for a way out of crisis without appearing to compromise with the West; country faces more Western sanctions; Ukraine rebels release bodies and flight recorders from downed plane.

headline.print_headline: Russia’s Message on Jet: Conciliation and Bluster

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Andrew Roth and Alexandra Odynova from Moscow; David M. Herszenhorn from Kiev; Sabrina Tavernise and Noah Sneider from Torez, Ukraine; and Chris Buckley from Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.

docs.snippet: The downing of Malaysia Airlines Flight 17 rippled across multiple continents, bringing home in vivid relief the consequences of a struggle that had seemed far removed for many.
docs.lead_paragraph: The downing of Malaysia Airlines Flight 17 rippled across multiple continents, bringing home in vivid relief the consequences of a struggle that had seemed far removed for many.
docs.abstract: Downing of Malaysia Airlines Flight 17 in Ukraine ripples across multiple continents, bringing home in vivid relief consequences of struggle in country that seemed far removed from many; news of plane being shot down spurs confusion, anger, grief and disbelief, as well as charges and countercharges of who was responsible; American intelligence agencies believe missile was shot from Russian side of border, and separatists say they brought down plane themselves.

docs.lead_paragraph: Bodies from the downed Malaysia Airlines jet were delivered to the eastern Ukrainian city of Kharkiv on Tuesday, but officials said that the remains of victims may still be buried in the wreckage.
docs.abstract: Bodies and flight recorders recovered from crash site of Malaysia Airlines Flight 17 are delivered safely from rebel control to Ukrainian city Kharkiv; forensics officials raise strong possibility that remains of many victims are still buried in wreckage and that identification could take weeks or months to complete.

headline.print_headline: More Bodies Possible at Ukraine Crash Site, Forensics Officials Say

docs.snippet: President Vladimir V. Putin blocked the import of some food and agricultural products for a year, an attempt to hit back at Western sanctions without punishing Russian consumers.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Vladimir V. Putin blocked the import of some food and agricultural products for a year, an attempt to hit back at Western sanctions without punishing Russian consumers.
docs.abstract: Russian Pres Vladimir V Putin gives his government broad mandate to issue one-year bans on food and agricultural imports, retaliation for Western sanctions over events in Ukraine; includes proviso that bans be lifted if they drive up prices or cause undue dependence on a single source; decree does not name specific products or countries to be banned.

headline.main: Putin Bans Some Imports as Payback for Sanctions
headline.print_headline: Putin Bans Some Imports as Payback for Sanctions

docs.snippet: For the Dutch, the prospect that Russian-backed separatists might be responsible for the loss of Malaysia Airlines Flight 17 poses a dilemma.
docs.lead_paragraph: For the Dutch, the prospect that Russian-backed separatists might be responsible for the loss of Malaysia Airlines Flight 17 poses a dilemma.
docs.abstract: Netherlands finds itself thrust squarely into unaccustomed role at center of realpolitik of the crisis in Ukraine after downing of Malaysia Airlines Flight 17, as 189 Dutch nationals were killed in the crash; prospect that Russian-backed separatists might be responsible for crash poses major dilemma for Dutch, as Russia is country's third largest trade partner.

headline.main: The Netherlands, a Nation in Mourning but Mindful of Ties to Russia
headline.print_headline: Dutch in Mourning but Mindful of Ties to Russia
